HTTP 
\b request
\b0  methods normally used in RESTful api:\
common: GET (used for retrieval of an existing resource), \
PUT (used for retrieval of an existing resource), \
POST (used for creation of a new resource), \
DELETE (used for deletion of an existing resource)\
\
Resource creation request uri is normally the collection URI of an entity with POST  method. Response of successful creation contains the id of the newly created resource.\
\
less common: HEAD, OPTIONS\
\
Idempotent methods (safely repeatable): GET,PUT,DELETE\
Non-idempotent methods (cannot be repeated safely): POST \
\
HTTP 
\b Response
\b0 :\
Normally XML or JSON with http HEADERs and STATUS codes.\
